nyon mongs|The essentially pure nature of mind is obscured and afflicted by various psychological defilements known as the afflicted mental states, which destroy the mind’s peace and composure. Included among them are the primary afflictions of fundamental ignorance, attachment, aversion, pride, doubt, and twenty subsidiary afflictions.
kun nas nyong mongs pa|The essentially pure nature of mind is obscured and afflicted by various psychological defilements known as the afflicted mental states, which destroy the mind’s peace and composure. Included among them are the primary afflictions of fundamental ignorance, attachment, aversion, pride, doubt, and twenty subsidiary afflictions.
sems las byung ba'i nye ba'i nyon mongs pa|The essentially pure nature of mind is obscured and afflicted by various psychological defilements known as the afflicted mental states, which destroy the mind’s peace and composure. Included among them are the primary afflictions of fundamental ignorance, attachment, aversion, pride, doubt, and twenty subsidiary afflictions.
nyon mongs|Desire, hatred and anger, dullness, pride, and jealousy, as well as all their derivatives, said to number 84,000. Also translated “passions.”
nyon mongs|Literally “pain,” “torment,” or “affliction.” In Buddhist Hybrid Sanskrit it means literally “impurity” or “depravity.” In its technical use in Buddhism it means any negative quality in the mind that causes continued existence in saṃsāra. The basic three kleśas are ignorance, attachment, and aversion.\naffliction
kun nas nyon mongs pa|The process of karma, afflictions of the mind, and suffering.
nyon mongs pa|A type of mental imperfection. The most basic afflictions are attachment, aversion, and confusion.
nyon mongs|Negative qualities in the mind, the basic three being ignorance, attachment, and aversion.
nyon mongs pa|The mental states which cause unrest in the mind, distorting the view of reality.
nyon mongs pa med pa nyon mongs pa dang bcas pa thams cad yang dag par 'du ba|Name of the 106th meditative stability.
