jo bo rje|The Bengali Buddhist master (980–1054) who came to Tibet, and whose pupils founded the Kadampa tradition.
a ti sha|Atiśa Dīpaṃkara­śrī­jñāna (982–1054 C.E.), often referred to in Tibetan as {jo bo}, “(The) Lord,” was a renowned figure in the history of Tibetan Buddhism famous for coming to Tibet and revitalizing Buddhism there during the early eleventh century.
