byang chub snying po|The place where Śakyamuni Buddha achieved awakening and where countless other Buddhas are said to have achieved awakening. This is understood to be located under the bodhi tree in present-day Bodhgaya, India.
byang chub kyi snying po|The place where Śakyamuni Buddha achieved awakening and where countless other Buddhas are said to have achieved awakening. This is understood to be located under the bodhi tree in present-day Bodhgaya, India.
byang chub kyi snying po|Haribhadra defines it as “a place used as a seat, where the maṇḍa, here ‘essence,’ of enlightenment is present.” See Lamotte, p. 198, n. 105. The main “seat of enlightenment” is the spot under the bo tree at Buddha Gaya, where the Buddha sat and attained unexcelled, perfect enlightenment. It is not to be confused with bodhimaṇḍala, “circle of enlightenment.”
byang chub snying po|"The essence of enlightenment.” The spot in Bodhgaya where the Buddha attained enlightenment.
