khor yug|In Buddhist cosmology this mountain range forms an outer ring at the edge of the flat disc that is the world. These mountains prevent the ocean from overflowing. In other contexts this name can refer to the entire disc of the world, the paradises above it, or, as in the Kṣiti­garbha Sūtra, to a mountain that contains the hells, also known as the Vaḍaba submarine mountain of fire.
