zag pa|A term of Jain origin, meaning “inflows.” It refers to uncontrolled thoughts as a result of being influenced by sensory objects and thus being sullied or defiled. It is also defined as “outflows,” hence the Tibetan {zag pa} (“leaks”) as the mind is “flowing out” toward the sensory objects.
