dran pa nye bar gzhag pa bzhi|The four applications of mindfulness are (1) the application of mindfulness which, with regard to the physical body, observes the physical body; (2) the application of mindfulness which, with regard to feelings, observes feelings; (3) the application of mindfulness which, with regard to the mind, observes the mind; and (4) the application of mindfulness which, with regard to phenomena, observes phenomena. In the present sūtra, these can be found listed in http://read.84000.co/translation/UT22084-031-002.html#UT22084-031-002-158 and detailed in http://read.84000.co/translation/UT22084-031-002.html#UT22084-031-002-949.
