tshangs pa'i gzer bu chen po|Or “Great Spike of Purity,” the name of a bodhisattva. Possibly śaṅku is a misreading or misspelling of sanatku which would be “the bodhisattva Sanatkumāra” (Pali. Sanaṅkumāra) who was a being of the class of Mahābrahmās−in Vedic legend, one of the four or seven “mind-born” sons of Brahmā−and who appears in various suttas in the Pali canon.
