pha rol tu phyin pa|Also translated as “transcendences.” The term is used to define the actions of a bodhisattva. The six perfections are: generosity, discipline, patience, diligence, concentration and wisdom.
pha rol tu phyin pa drug|The trainings of the bodhisattva path: generosity, discipline, patience, diligence, concentration, and knowledge.
