rang sangs rgyas|Someone who obtains personal liberation through very little or no instruction from others; “solitary buddha” in some interpretations.
rang sangs rgyas|Literally, “buddha for himself,” or “solitary realiser.” Those who attain buddhahood in a time when the Buddha’s doctrine is no longer available in the world, and who remain either in solitude or amongst peers, without teaching the path to liberation to others. They are sometimes called “rhinoceros-like” for their preference to stay in solitude.\npratyeka
